# TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE & CODING INSTRUCTIONS

## Project Directory Schema
Maintain the repository strictly to this design:
- `extension/` -> manifest.json, background.js, content.js
- `extension/sidepanel/` -> sidepanel.html, sidepanel.css, sidepanel.js
- `backend/api/` -> extract.js, sync.js

## Security & Extension Rules (Manifest V3)
- NO Remotely Hosted Code: All script logic must be packaged locally inside the extension folder.
- NO Direct API Requests to LLM Providers from Client: The extension frontend must never fetch `api.openai.com` or `generativelanguage.googleapis.com` directly. Route all requests through the `backend/api/` runtime.

## Code Style
- Write asynchronous code with clean `async/await` patterns wrapper-protected by explicit `try/catch` handlers.
- On backend failure, the sidepanel UI must gracefully display an actionable retry component.
- Avoid raw `innerHTML` injections from LLM responses to mitigate Cross-Site Scripting (XSS). Sanitize or parse markdown safely using standard, isolated web component DOM nodes.